{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_013t31nxGkAmUaRmp8fKJaHy","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/027-web-chat-message-fade-in-animation/plan.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"98537608-2ff0-4143-81a2-60a093ccd611","uuid":"163b98ac-190c-45d2-8987-705815a88cbf","timestamp":"2026-03-22T17:34:04.787Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/027-web-chat-message-fade-in-animation/plan.md","oldString":"- [ ] Add `@keyframes fade-in` definition to `public/styles.css`\n- [ ] Add `animation: fade-in 0.25s ease-out both` to `.message` rule\n- [ ] Run tests to confirm no regressions","newString":"- [x] Add `@keyframes fade-in` definition to `public/styles.css`\n- [x] Add `animation: fade-in 0.25s ease-out both` to `.message` rule\n- [x] Run tests to confirm no regressions","originalFile":"# Plan — F-027: Web Chat Message Fade-In Animation\n\n## Overview\nAdd CSS fade-in animation to new chat messages in the web admin panel.\nPure CSS change — no backend or JS modifications needed.\n\n## Key Components\n- `@keyframes fade-in`: defines opacity 0→1 transition\n- `.message` animation: applies the keyframe animation\n- Acceptance criterion 3 (no animation on page load existing messages):\n  CSS animations on `.message` fire when the element is inserted into the DOM.\n  The welcome message (appended at `init()`) will also animate — this is acceptable\n  per the spec which says \"existing history messages\" (pre-loaded from server state).\n  Since this app loads no server-side message history on page load, criterion 3 is\n  inherently satisfied — the welcome message is dynamically inserted and animating\n  it is visually expected.\n\n## Files to Modify\n- `public/styles.css` — add `@keyframes fade-in` and `animation` property to `.message`\n\n## Animation Design\n- Duration: 0.25s (snappy, not distracting)\n- Easing: `ease-out` (decelerates — natural for appearing elements)\n- Fill mode: `both` (ensures opacity:0 before animation starts, opaque after)\n- Keyframes: `from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(4px); }` → `to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }`\n- Small translateY adds subtle depth without being distracting\n\n## Tasks\n- [ ] Add `@keyframes fade-in` definition to `public/styles.css`\n- [ ] Add `animation: fade-in 0.25s ease-out both` to `.message` rule\n- [ ] Run tests to confirm no regressions\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":26,"oldLines":6,"newStart":26,"newLines":6,"lines":[" - Small translateY adds subtle depth without being distracting"," "," ## Tasks","-- [ ] Add `@keyframes fade-in` definition to `public/styles.css`","-- [ ] Add `animation: fade-in 0.25s ease-out both` to `.message` rule","-- [ ] Run tests to confirm no regressions","+- [x] Add `@keyframes fade-in` definition to `public/styles.css`","+- [x] Add `animation: fade-in 0.25s ease-out both` to `.message` rule","+- [x] Run tests to confirm no regressions"]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
